Days after several lives were lost and buildings destroyed due to a fuel tanker fire at Upper Iweka Road in Onitsha, Anambra State woke up to another fire disaster at Omagba, also in Onitsha. The PUNCH reports that the fire incident involved another fuel tanker and that it happened in the early hours of Friday morning along the Enugu-Onitsha Expressway by Bessoy filling station, Onitsha Police Commissioner, John Abang, who confirmed the incident, said that men of the fire service responded faster to the fire incident than they did on Wednesday. READ ALSO: Another tanker explodes in Omagba, Onitsha See photos:     Photos by Tony Okafor